commit.message: Horizontal screenshots

Added screenshots

Added app screenshots

App screenshot

For app screenshots

Bundle Identifier, Certificates

Set things up on iTunes Connect and downloaded certificates and keys.

v.1 get app analytics

Used Fabrics Answers to get app analytics.

Official v.1

Changed some UI to make iPhone 5s version look better.

official version 1

The official code for version 1. Now I'll generate screenshots for app submission onto the apple store.

start v.2

Start version 2 from here. Now I'll make submission for my version 1, and take away the non-functional day counts on the congratulations page.

user default for one-time alert controllers

Used user default that can be accessed globally and persist data, so that 3 alert controllers would only show once after users download the app. Before, the alerts would show once every time the app is called from the background.

Prepare for day count feature

added notes to start adding this feature

Housekeeping

Deleted extra code blocks never used. Delete extra comments. Formatting better.

Singleton

Used a singleton to temporarily store data from DailyStartSurvey, and only create new core data selfHelpDay and save selfHelpDay in DailyEndSurvey. This prevents users to save "half a day" in personal history, which was a major problem. Added app icon to launch screen. Did some housekeeping.

one-time alert controllers & polish personal history appeal

Show some alert controllers only once upon app installation. Tableview automatically scrolls to the bottom in personal history view controller. Perfected the alignment of personal history first row.

Polish look

Added background images, redid constraints, final look is done!

format of personal history

changed date format and constraints to align the first row and the rest of the rows.

MVP ready!

All core data is shown in personal history now! Passed on selfHelpDay data onto the next each of the 3 view controllers (music, exercise, and journal), and pass on to daily end survey. Added background images for some view controllers, so now it looks more polished.

Alert controllers and congratulations page

Changed cursor color.
Beautified the congratulations page with background image, text color, and text layout.
Added 3 alert controllers for:
- “you can’t edit the journal, but you can swipe left to delete each journal”
-“Make sure your phone is not on silent mode.”
- “You haven’t typed anything in journal entry yet.”

added 2 alert controllers & minor change in personal history

Displayed self care method in personal history.
Added an alert controllers to only allow numbers from 0-999 for InputTimeSpent. Added an alert controller for  deleting individual journals.

Core Data, display on personal history

Got most display working now. Todo: fix self care method displayed and avoid creating a new self help day twice when there's only once.

personal history start

Prevented a music view crash. Started on core data for personal history view controller

actual reverse journal

Reversed the display and delete functions for individual journals. Before, only tableview cell display was reversed.

date format

Convert date to my desired format

App icon

Made an app icon and re-sized for all. Also debugged the warning for storyboard

finish music screen

make music stop when the same cell is tapped again. Added swipe-to-delete action for exercise cells

image in music view controller

Added images in each music cell. Resized cells in main storyboard and changed some background colors to dark gray. Reorganized some labels.

Fixed journal display bug and added MP3 files

Fixed the bug of placeholder text showing in journal history in gray. Now journal history displays the correct user input in black again. Added 7 self care music in MP3 format with credit in my resource page.

4 tab bar icons and journal text view border

Added the 4 tab bar icons in all 3 resolutions. Made a credit document linked at the bottom of the resources view controller. Added border for the journal text view with the same style as that of the journal text field. Added a placeholder text to help get the user in a flow and understand what the text view is for.

Finished resources

Put 8 resources on the resources page. Used switch cases to open the correct link when user taps a row
